      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUSH HOUR (1) struggled to get involved last start after settling well back at this track, but prior to that won by 3 lengths at Geelong (25.78) beating Maximum Damage in a Grade 5 on July 10. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Looks the one to beat on her best form. ZIPPING MAUDIE (7) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by a long neck at this track in a handy 30.93 beating Paw Helion. Bold showing expected again. PAW GREGSON (2) turned in a modest effort most recently when sixth at this track over 525m behind Show Me Style (31.31) in a Grade 5. Has performed well from this box with a win and six minor placings to his name from 12 starts. Bold showing expected. OUT THE WINDOW (5) has strong claims after a long-odds top-three finish last time out.",
